<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_da6274b0-ee65-4a0a-9fe7-99026da37213" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>10.2.30</sptc><title id="_d5ee2ac3-f065-4127-9f66-45aee0ec9761">Drainage riser connection</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_3b09bb9b-3ffd-43ea-99c4-bfe21fb48a58" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ef2210fb-31e1-4af8-94f9-9a324489e5a6">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4664_0.7.0.xml#_a207c296-a8b3-4ffe-81e0-a598ccc4b4d8" id="_8881fbd3-826d-47f8-8752-c7438f574a80" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">preformed shower base</xref> is used, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4765_0.5.0.xml#_afdcf6a5-e364-4a91-bbc8-47678401204b" id="_de6b7fcb-2f64-457f-a37c-c561e07c6735" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage riser</xref> must be connected to the tray with a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1519_0.5.0.xml#_02296d09-c6a7-41f4-a398-1f059045818c" id="_eb66825f-4ced-4ef7-ab0b-e7b1956dc697" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproof</xref> joint.</p></subclause><subclause id="_a9e26b4c-7488-4900-a1e8-c15da547c52b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b14b404e-f187-4b03-8fbf-c423e924a7c6">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Where an in situ shower tray is used, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_2691c48b-c65f-4ff4-950b-885ee6f67cc4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> must be able to form a permanent <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1519_0.5.0.xml#_02296d09-c6a7-41f4-a398-1f059045818c" id="_b8df745e-3e4a-4502-8917-612a8a3db3e4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproof</xref> seal to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4765_0.5.0.xml#_afdcf6a5-e364-4a91-bbc8-47678401204b" id="_7951b3a2-90f1-4906-b6dd-a8fd132254a4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage riser</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4655_0.3.0.xml#_2e5370a3-7f80-4486-8af6-4387bbf9acce" id="_2d804f3b-a7ee-4a21-bf74-4b24f24984db" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage flange</xref> (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4766_0.15.0.xml#_a496a89b-84ce-4d88-be86-1b189d12a319" id="_f6ba1855-729f-46c3-a2aa-073a485ce438" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 10.2.29</xref>).</p></subclause></clause>